The paper discusses techniques for performing static analysis on LLVM IR, which is a representation used by modern compilers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on energy consumption for embedded platforms, which suggests that it may also belong to the Embedded Systems (cs.EMBD) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges of determining energy costs for executing LLVM IR program segments, which suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method for energy-aware software development, which suggests that it may also belong to the Architecture (cs.AR) sub-category.
